[src:typescript-docs/classes] Classes, methods, and fields in TypeScript may be *abstract*.
[src:typescript-docs/classes] An *abstract method* or *abstract field* is one that hasn’t had an implementation provided.
[src:typescript-docs/classes] These members must exist inside an *abstract class*, which cannot be directly instantiated.
[src:typescript-docs/classes] The role of abstract classes is to serve as a base class for subclasses which do implement all the abstract members.
