[src:typescript-docs/generics] Remember, we said earlier that these type variables stand in for any and all types, so someone using this function could have passed in a `number` instead, which does not have a `.length` member.
[src:typescript-docs/generics] Let’s say that we’ve actually intended this function to work on arrays of `Type` rather than `Type` directly.
[src:typescript-docs/generics] Since we’re working with arrays, the `.length` member should be available.
